This paper presents an information retrieval-based approach to recover variable names in minified JS code, which involves searching for them in a large corpus of open-source JS code. This approach involves techniques from software engineering (SE) and programming languages (PL) to analyze and understand code, as well as information retrieval (IR) to search for relevant information in the corpus. Additionally, the paper discusses the accuracy and performance of the approach, which could fall under categories such as cryptography (CR) or machine learning (LG).
